WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.041 --> 00:00:01.334
Back in 2023,

00:00:01.334 --> 00:00:02.502
we were facing

00:00:02.502 --> 00:00:03.837
a really difficult time

00:00:03.837 --> 00:00:05.171
at support at Lyft.

00:00:05.171 --> 00:00:06.506
Rider base increased,

00:00:06.506 --> 00:00:07.924
our driver base was increasing,

00:00:07.924 --> 00:00:10.176
and this was super exciting for Lyft,

00:00:10.176 --> 00:00:10.969
but it felt like

00:00:10.969 --> 00:00:12.470
our current support system

00:00:12.470 --> 00:00:13.388
was not set up

00:00:13.388 --> 00:00:14.514
to handle this well.

00:00:17.642 --> 00:00:19.352
Our support queues

00:00:19.352 --> 00:00:20.937
were getting a bit overwhelmed.

00:00:20.937 --> 00:00:22.313
It was just a long time

00:00:22.313 --> 00:00:24.607
to wait and get an issue resolved

00:00:24.607 --> 00:00:26.317
for our riders and our drivers.

00:00:26.317 --> 00:00:26.985
We knew we needed

00:00:26.985 --> 00:00:27.902
to do something,

00:00:27.902 --> 00:00:30.280
but it wasn't clear yet what.

00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:31.781
There were definitely a lot of

00:00:31.781 --> 00:00:33.533
different models that we

00:00:33.533 --> 00:00:35.201
were considering using.

00:00:35.201 --> 00:00:36.786
Claude's personality

00:00:36.786 --> 00:00:39.539
is really what stuck out.

00:00:39.539 --> 00:00:40.540
When I was looking at

00:00:40.540 --> 00:00:42.625
the actual support interactions,

00:00:42.625 --> 00:00:43.710
there was just this

00:00:43.710 --> 00:00:45.628
more organic feeling.

00:00:45.628 --> 00:00:46.921
Our customers were

00:00:46.921 --> 00:00:48.673
conversing more and opening up

00:00:48.673 --> 00:00:49.340
about the issues

00:00:49.340 --> 00:00:50.175
that they were having.

00:00:50.175 --> 00:00:51.426
Customer resolution time

00:00:51.426 --> 00:00:53.261
decreased by 87%.

00:00:53.261 --> 00:00:54.387
So something that would have taken

00:00:54.387 --> 00:00:55.597
 30 plus minutes

00:00:55.597 --> 00:00:56.347
now sometimes

00:00:56.347 --> 00:00:57.307
that's even resolved

00:00:57.307 --> 00:00:58.933
in a matter of seconds.

00:01:01.394 --> 00:01:02.353
This feels like

00:01:02.353 --> 00:01:04.064
a transformational shift

00:01:04.064 --> 00:01:06.149
for Lyft customer support.

00:01:06.941 --> 00:01:08.276
Through using Claude

00:01:08.276 --> 00:01:09.652
for our AI assistant,

00:01:09.652 --> 00:01:10.945
we have been able to

00:01:10.945 --> 00:01:12.489
save millions of dollars

00:01:12.489 --> 00:01:13.531
on the support side

00:01:13.531 --> 00:01:15.158
that we’ve specifically focused on

00:01:15.158 --> 00:01:17.118
reinvesting back into our

00:01:17.118 --> 00:01:18.036
support agents

00:01:18.036 --> 00:01:19.954
to upskill them,

00:01:19.954 --> 00:01:21.372
to avoid burnout,

00:01:21.372 --> 00:01:22.665
empowering our agents

00:01:22.665 --> 00:01:25.001
to spend more time on the issues

00:01:25.001 --> 00:01:26.503
that require human care

00:01:26.503 --> 00:01:28.004
and infusing that layer

00:01:28.004 --> 00:01:29.255
of empathy and care,

00:01:29.255 --> 00:01:30.465
that's really important

00:01:30.465 --> 00:01:31.925
to us at Lyft.

